casebody.data:
In re FRANCE & CANADA S. S. CORPORATION. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 17, 1923.) No. 293. D. Goldstone and Plaherty, Turner & Strouse, all of New York City (Touis H. Strouse, of New York City, of counsel), for petitioner. George P. Nicholson, óf New York City (Charles J. Nehrbas, of New York City, of counsel), for respondent.

Before ROGERS, MANTON, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition dismissed in open court, on the ground that the matter lies in the discretion of the District Court; this court declining to decide the case on the merits.
